column5: anyone ever fish these lakes?..and if so which one is the best?
I fished them years ago for bass and one of the lakes was unbelievable for big ones but I just can't remember which one  I will try to look at a map and see if I can remember
you know what they say...gitter done.......go fish them fro mwhat Im told you ll figure out which one has the largest pretty fast
I have fished Big Whitefish a few times.  Its still pretty undeveloped for a muskoka lake, so I found the bite to be pretty good.  I caught a few meaty smallies there last fall.
I'm actually talking about the lakes up towards kingston
yeah thats the ones I am talking about too  the three of them are beside each other

eyefish, PM me after this weekend to remind me and I will update you.  Going there this weekend with the CBAF.  Looking forward to it.  Went last year and had a fun time - but unless you mean big fish as in 2 lber, I didn't see any of those mythical creatures.  Hopefully this year will encounter a few.  Charles
yup 2.0000000000001` I can fell it the senko bite is strong with you
Never been there before but I'll be prefishing Friday for a CBAF Tourney Saturday, should be a great weekend with a bunch of great fisherman, let you know how it turns out Richard
What if I was to say that I was fishing there this weekend in the CBAF tourny too?
I'd say best of luck cuz your going to need it HAHA & see you there Richard
To answer my own question...cranberry lake was on fire today..weighed in almost 17 pounds...and caught well over 30 largemouth! I just wish I lived closer to kingston!
